{
  "stem": "19218.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "This was the first one that I witnessed, really, besides the one on the march from our city where they killed the rabbi and-- and the doctor-- and the physician.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And of course, we-- they loaded us in boxcars-- boxcars.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And-- and-- and my father, mother, and we all happened to have been-- we all went with the same transport.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So we were all in the same car, boxcar.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I remember-- I do not recall the days or nights that it took to get to Auschwitz-- but I remember that my father turned completely white in the boxcar.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I mean, he was a young man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "My father, at the time, was 55 years old, and so was my mother.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But they both turned white.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And of course, when we arrived in Auschwitz, the selection started, because the-- the-- the-- the-- the noises, the voices, the yelling-- aus, raus, raus, raus.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And immediately they started beating us, immediately.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They had canes in their-- in their hands, and they started beating us already.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "The one [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] story, the one-- the one action which I have witnessed in there-- there was a very, very old couple.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Of course-- of course, when I arrived in-- in-- in Auschwitz in 1943, I was 17 years old, January of 1943.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "So I really-- almost anyone older than I was old.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And they just wouldn't part.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "They were just holding down to each other, holding onto each other.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And they were beating them with the canes over their heads.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "You could see the blood on the white hair.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "They just wouldn't-- and finally they took canes with a-- with a hook at the end, and they just-- around their necks, and they just pulled them apart.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "This is the arrival.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
